TeleMasters [JSE:TLM], one of the best performing small-cap stocks on the JSE in 2018, announced a fall in revenue and profit in a trading update on Monday saying, saying SIM card customers were cancelling contracts as usage habits change. Total revenue declined from R113.5m in 2018  to R100m in the year ended June 30, 2109. Operating profit decreased from R4.5m in 2018 to R151 925 in 2019. A positive tax charge, however, boosted profit for the period to just over R1m, about a third of what is was in the previous year. The IT company – which offers voice, data and cloud-based infrastructure and services, said it had diversified its offering, with its current product strategy centered around driving customers to the cloud. 